Plugin Conflicts
Plugins can conflict because they:

Modify the same functionality
Use incompatible JavaScript libraries
Compete for database resources
Override the same hooks

Diagnosing conflicts:

Note the symptoms (error messages, broken features)
Deactivate all plugins
Reactivate one by one, testing each time
Identify the conflicting combination
Decide: replace one, find alternative, or contact support

Preventing conflicts:

Minimise plugin count (each one adds risk)
